Date:   Wed Jun 17 13:14:38 2026 -0400

    feat(cms)(per-page-content): RichText + six Page schemas + HomePage + FormDefinition placeholder + per-page/per-form defaults
    
    Land the typed per-Page + per-Form content schemas (ADR 0008, settled #5,
    registration-launch Branch 5.1) and their bundled defaults — the typed homes
    the flat-translation god-bag's per-page copy migrates into (Branch 5.4) and the
    seed content getPage/getForm read through (Branch 5.3).
    
    - RichText: a closed inline-token model (text / bold / link via TaggedUnion),
      NOT arbitrary HTML; a link href is a validated LinkHref (https | mailto only,
      reusing the ExternalHttpsUrl XSS boundary).
    - AboutPage, FaqPage, GivePage, ContactPage, VolunteerPage, ArchivePage, HomePage
      — each modelling its real structure; list items carry ListItemId in IdListArray.
    - FormDefinition: a typed PLACEHOLDER (title + optional intro) so Branch 5.3's
      per-form read path has a real decode boundary; Branch 6 grows the field graph.
    - Per-page/per-form bundled defaults, authored encoded and decoded through each
      schema; list-item ids minted with newListItemId.
    - pages/schema.test.ts: per-page default round-trips, RichText token round-trip,
      LinkHref accept/reject (https+mailto vs javascript/data/http/relative/creds),
      closed-token-set rejection, and present-but-empty hard-decode-error cases.

